title: Pic la Selle
content:
Pic la Selle (French pronunciation: [pik la sɛl]; Haitian Creole: Pik Lasel), also called Morne La Selle, is the highest peak in Haiti at 2,680 metres (8,793 ft) above sea level.[2] The mountain is part of the Chaîne de la Selle mountain range.  It is located in the Ouest administrative department.
